programmes.show_description: Haunted Calling: Hear the stories of ghost hunters, as they share their personal experiences from the past that put them on the path to a paranormal profession. (S1, ep 2)
In Nova Scotia, a former naval officer sees five bright lights in the skies and a cigar-shaped object behind them. (S12, ep 13)
Strange light patterns are seen in Texas. In France, a man's knee injury is suddenly healed after an odd encounter. (S2, ep 14)
Giorgio Tsoukalos takes a look back at the most compelling investigations of all, and events that he believes represent real encounters with extraterrestrial visitors.
Mystery In The Bayou: With them not catching any Gators, Troy and Terral test a radical new strategy, while Jacob's new deckhand tries to prove his worth. (S11, ep 4)
Gators and Ghost Towns: As Troy, Chase and Bill mount an airboat to hunt an area where pythons are raiding alligator nests, an unfortunate error could leave them stranded. (S2, ep 4)
Unforgiven: Rich makes a glaring error that could see him fired. Plus, a kooky cowboy arrives at the counter and Ashley reacts to bad manners in the pawn shop queue. (S8, ep 3)
Join antiques expert and presenter David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal or take a chance at auction instead? (S9, ep 20)
Hangar 18: UFO Warehouse: Experts claim that UFO wreckage is stored in a top-secret facility in Ohio. Former employees spin a tale of alien bodies and flying saucer debris. (S1, ep 20)
Alien Encounters: An examination of what ufology calls 'trace cases', where physical material from an encounter is analysed to determine if it is evidence of an alien contact. (S1, ep 21)
Sightings of the 70s: Accounts from a number of UFO sightings that took place in the 1970s, including the most famous of all intergalactic crashes: Roswell. (S1, ep 22)
Alien Engineering (Part 1 of 2): What would happen if a UFO did land on Earth and humans found it? Engineers create a 'spaceship' to see how alien technology could work. (S1, ep 14)
Alien Engineering (Part 2 of 2): Laser weapons and tele-transporters would probably all be fitted to an alien spaceship, but what if they could be used by humans too? (S1, ep 15)
What Lies Below: UAPs have been seen entering the ocean at high speeds - and since our oceans can be as deep as six miles, were the UAPs simply trying to get home? (S1, ep 9)
The Paradox: As the Fermi Paradox states, the likelihood of advanced life in the universe is surprisingly high - so why haven't we had any contact with extraterrestrial life? (S1, ep 10)
Langenburg: Expert Chris Rutkowski, home to the largest UFO research archive, sets the scene and explains an unexplained event. (S1, ep 7)
Sometimes, the mysterious unidentified objects people see in the sky touch down and leave physical evidence behind. (S1, ep 6)
Crocodile Monster, Tiktok USO, and Ghost Dog Collar Removal: The team investigate a legendary man-eating croc, glowing lights in Mexico and chilling footage of a pair of dogs. (S3, ep 10)
Congressional UFOs, New Nessie and Zombie Fish: Dive into a video from the US Navy that proves once and for all that UFOs exist and examine an alleged Loch Ness monster sighting. (S3, ep 1)
Check out America's 1500 feet tall atomic tower, uncover the lost village of the damned and embark on a hunt for dinosaur fossils... from outer space? (S5, ep 20)
World's Deadliest Threats: Mysterious satellite images reveal China's hidden terror camps and provide access to America's top secret apocalypse pyramid. (S6, ep 1)
Monsters of Diamond Desert: Satellites capture unusual images including markings in the desert, while a strange symbol could be a portal into a lost South American civilisation. (S6, ep 2)
The Loch Ness Monster: Despite centuries of sightings, the most infamous deep-sea monster remains unidentified. Does the Loch Ness Monster exist and, if so, what could it be? (S4, ep 1)
The Assassination of JFK: In 1963, President John F Kennedy is assassinated. A suspect is captured but investigators and amateur sleuths still investigate alternative theories. (S4, ep 3)
The Lost Colony of Roanoke: In 1587, settlers land on Roanoke Island to establish the first English colony in America, but vanish without a trace and leave only cryptic clues. (S4, ep 4)
An Eye for a Eye: From strict, brutal codes of Hammurabi, to the secretly malevolent evil eye. History is full of remarkable stories of acts committed in the name of revenge. (S2, ep 3)
The Catalaunian Plains: Attila, king of the Huns, faces strongman of the Roman Empire, Generalissimo Aetius. But their terrible battle ends in a bloodbath, with no clear victory. (S2, ep 5)
Evil Places: From dark forests to haunted houses, explore the places where bad things repeatedly and inexplicably happen. (S1, ep 1)
Mysterious Structures: A look at how Giza's Great Pyramid and Coral Castle were built. Were they were deliberately constructed in a mysterious way? (S1, ep 2)
The Hat of Teeth, the Killer Shockbox and the Amazonian Quiver: Examine a hat emblazoned with teeth, a box with the power to kill and a golden quiver from a Macedonian tomb. (S2, ep 9)
Hangar 18: UFO Warehouse: Experts claim that UFO wreckage is stored in a top-secret facility in Ohio. Former employees spin a tale of alien bodies and flying saucer debris. (S1, ep 20)
Alien Encounters: An examination of what ufology calls 'trace cases', where physical material from an encounter is analysed to determine if it is evidence of an alien contact. (S1, ep 21)
Sightings of the 70s: Accounts from a number of UFO sightings that took place in the 1970s, including the most famous of all intergalactic crashes: Roswell. (S1, ep 22)
Series investigating compelling UFO and alien cases by opening previously off-limits secret files. Does the mysterious Blue Planet Project hold the answers? (S1, ep 1)
Amped Up in Tampa: Motorcyclists fight with an angry driver and find themselves staring down the barrel of a gun and a semi-truck is no match for high-speed winds from a tornado. (S1, ep 3)
Burning Down the Rv: A driver and a motorcyclist in Florida play a dangerous game of cat and mouse and a couple in Canada plummet their truck into an icy lake. (S1, ep 4)
A Tale of Two Engines: Mike takes on a rare Hertz Shelby Mustang for his friend's brother, but the badly damaged car might be too far-gone. (S5, ep 4)
...Henry's Wreck-trospective. Henry and Sam start at Bristol Classic Car Show, where they acquire a quirky car from the 1970s. (S1, ep 1)
...Henry's Wreck-trospective.The Stratford Wreck- Trospective: Henry's Wreck-trospective dives headfirst into the archives to celebrate the very best bits from the series. (S1, ep 2)
The vintage restorers return for season four, challenging themselves to make money out of other people's automotive junk and classic collectables. (S4, ep 4)
Ford Orion: Everyone wants a classic Ford, so the team target an Orion. There's just one problem - the steering wheel is on the wrong side. (S3, ep 5)
Action Packed Pawn: A ceramic owl made by Pablo Picasso sends Rick cock-a-hoot. Meanwhile, Beatlemania takes over the shop as a Yellow Submarine poster arrives on the counter.
Jurassic Pawn: Chum gets into the teen spirit when a piece of Kurt Cobain memorabilia finds its way into the shop. Rick takes a swing at a National League Championship ring.
Rick Vs. The Globe Of Death: Rick and Chum get a genius package containing letters signed by Albert Einstein. Chum and Corey marvel at replicas of Thor's helmet and hammer.
Trading Places: When an injury sidelines Allen at the shop, Ton goes rogue at auction, ignoring his partner's advice and making risky purchases. (S4, ep 6)
Flying Ton, Creeping Allen: When a group of thugs try to bully Ton and Allen, the guys fight back, leading to a violent showdown and the discovery of a rare Bornean blowgun. (S4, ep 8)
Whip it Good: With a motocross bike and a rare stock whip up for grabs, Ton and Allen face their former employee Carolyn, who knows all their tricks and is out for revenge. (S4, ep 7)
Machine Gun Ton: Ton and Allen battle a pair of vicious female auction hunters who have an axe to grind. (S4, ep 9)
Lego My Locker: Darrell must deal with Kimber's eyes on a competitor, Dusty unpacks what could be the ultimate assistant and Rene pulls off one of his greatest profits. (S14, ep 8)
Reign or Shine: King Darrell strives to defend his throne, but Rene and Casey signal their intentions to undermine his plans. Meanwhile, Kenny gets bowled over by his locker. (S14, ep 9)
The King of Montebowl-o: Barry turns up to auction armed with a present for a certain hustler. Meanwhile, Brandi and Bozek get a firm grip on a smaller unit. (S14, ep 10)
Here Comes the Calvin-ry!: Lisa dons her cowboy gear and brings her money sock along, while Rene sinks his teeth into an unassuming unit and Brandi goes on a scavenger hunt. (S14, ep 11)
Zip Tie Lies: Rene and Casey roll the dice on some sealed totes in San Bernardino, while Kenny stumbles over some odd-looking car parts and Lisa shields herself from disaster. (S14, ep 12)
Children of the Cornbread: Ivy does his utmost to intimidate the other buyers in Lancaster, while Brandi gives in to Bozek and Dusty goes up against the King to prove a point. (S14, ep 13)
Proxy Moxie: Barry uses a little-known tactic to snatch up a locker and it ties him up in knots. Meanwhile, Brandi shops in the bargain basement and Ivy lands a sizeable unit. (S14, ep 14)
Two for the Price of Dust: The big guns come out in Riverside, but Rene isn't having any of it. Darrell pushes his luck with a smaller locker and makes a neat profit. (S14, ep 15)
Hairy Situation: While a trip abroad brings new discoveries, the team is thrilled to find new evidence linking Lot Five and the Money Pit. (S11, ep 24)
Graveyard of Scatarie: Jeff MacKinnon's team searches Scatarie Island for The Feversham's lost fortune. Battling currents, they uncover artifacts that may lead to treasure. (S1, ep 3)
America: Once the flagship in the United States Lines, the SS America served her owners for 55 years until she was unceremoniously left abandoned in the Canary Islands. (6 of 6)
Two hikers take refuge from a storm in a haunted hut in Scotland and a California man's canine companion calls out from the other side. (S8, ep 9)
